          "explanation": "Isoniazid inhibits the endogenous syntheisis of Niacin so,the patient developed dermatitis,diarrhea,dementia. Prolonged treatment with Isoniazid leads to Pyridoxine deficiency,which is required for endogenous synthesis of niacin Reference: Harpers illustrated biochemistry 30th edition",
