          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "Precursor tRNA is processed to form mature tRNA. Alterations during processing are of three types: nucloelytic reactions, nucleoside modifications, terminal additions of nucleotides. Chemical hydrolysis is not a pa of RNA processing. Poly A tailing and 5'capping occurs in the processing of RNA. Methylation and deamination are known to occur. Introns will be removed after cleavage in the process."
