          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "Dinitrophenol (DNP) a potent uncoupler is amphipathic and increase the permeability of the lipoid inner mitochondrial membrane to protons (H+), thus reducing the electrochemical potential and sho-circuiting the ATP synthase. In this way, oxidation can proceed without phosphorylation.Ref: MN Chatterjea Textbook of Medical Biochemistry, 8th edition, page no: 146",
