          "explanation": "* The Golgi apparatus functions in association with the endoplasmic reticulum. Small 'transpo vehicles' continuously pinch off from the endoplasmic reticulum and then fuse with the Golgi apparatus. * Thus, substances entrapped in the transpo vesicles are transpoed from the endoplasmic reticulum to the Golgi apparatus. * The transpoed substances are then processed in the Golgi apparatus to form lysosomes, secretory vesicles and other cytoplasmic components. * In sho, the Golgi apparatus brings about modification of proteins."
