          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Genes can be broadly divided into types based on their expression pattern: Constitutively expressed genes Regulated genes House-keeping genes Inducible/repressible Transcribed at a constant level Transcribed depending upon the environmental conditions Eg : Glycolytic enzymes Ribosomal RNA and proteins Eg : UDP-glucuronosyl transferase Lac I gene is constitutively regulated. Lac Z, Lac Y and Lac A genes are regulated by induction/repression.",
