          "explanation": "Ans. B. CyclooxygenaseCyclooxygenase is required for the synthesis of prostaglandins by arachidonic acid. Aspirin, indomethacin, brufen, phenyl butazone and other NSAIDS inhibits COX (Cyclooxygenase). Aspirin inhibits COX of both PGHS-1 and PGHS-2 by acetylation",
          "hint": "Topic: Enzymes"
