          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Side chain (R) of amino acid which have pure alkyl groups (e.g. methyl), or pure aromatic group, are nonpolar.\nSide chain (R) of amino acid which have functional groups, such as hydroxyl, carboxyl, amino, amides and acids, imparts more polar characteristic to amino acid."
